column5: Beautiful report! Some great looking fish there. Thanks for sharing.
Great pics and report.  Some lovely browns there!!
wow....great lookin brownies....looks like a nice area too....the browns have amazing color
Amazing stuff.  You've got yourself a gem of a stream there
Love brown butter.
Thanks folks.  'Tis the season for big browns.  Doesn't last long in this area.
Great fish and outing.  I cant wait to get my first legit brown on a fly.  Great pan shots. I like that feature on my camera.
So the myth of dirty water doesn't hold true??The higher,the dirtier,the better.Great report!!At least for browns I guess.
That coupled with the right fly and technique definitely gets the job done.
wow - beauty fish.  well done
This is a magnificent report with some truly spectacular fly caught browns. Thank you I am green with envy. If your ever looking for someone to join you feel free to PM me.

No idea where abouts you live, but if you're headed to this area and want to get out, shoot me a message.  I live in Guelph, plenty of decent trout fishing around here.  These fish aren't from around here though...  The least I could do is show you some setups and techniques anyways.
Nice job Dave, water looks up put pretty clear.
I'm confused...I can't find Nunyer Creek on any maps???
Its there if you look hard enough.  I'll post a treasure map later dude
Was pretty mucky in the morning.  By the time I decided to start snapping pics it had cleared up quite a bit.
Gotta love rivers that clear up that quickly.  Upper Pine is very similar.
Very nice report, gotta love Browns
Now that would make for a great weekend. Nothing better than having a gem like that all to yourself...
Stunning browns bud. Wish I had the time
Some real beauty fish there. Great report
some great shots...  resident browns have spectacular color displays...
Beautiful fish!!!
